free.freechess
Class SeekInfoStruct

java.lang.Object
  free.util.Struct
      free.freechess.SeekInfoStruct

public class SeekInfoStruct
extends Struct

A structure holding parsed information from a seekinfo line. More information about the format is available in the "help iv_seekinfo" file on the Free Internet Chess Server (http://www.freechess.org).

                      int maxRating,
                      boolean isAutomaticAccept,
                      boolean isFormulaUsed)
Creates a new SeekInfoStruct with the specified arguments.

Parameters:
canAcceptSeek - true if the user can accept the seek, false otherwise.
index - The seek index.
name - The handle of the seeking player.
titles - The titles of the player, ORed into an int.
rating - The rating of the player.
provShow - The seeker's rating provshow character, 'E' is estimated, 'P' if provisional and ' ' if neither.
time - The time of the sought game, in minutes.
inc - The increment of the sought game, in seconds.
isRated - The ratedness of the sought game.
matchType - The type of the match (either variant or rating type - "suicide", "lightning", "blitz" etc.).
color - The requested color. 'W' if white, 'B' if black and '?' if doesn't care.
minRating - The minimum rating of the sought opponent.
maxRating - The maximum rating of the sought opponent.
isAutomaticAccept - true if the acceptance of the seek is automatic, false if manual.
isFormulaUsed - true if the you must pass the seeker's formula to accept the offer.
Method Detail

parseSeekInfoLine

public static SeekInfoStruct parseSeekInfoLine(java.lang.String line)
Parses the given seekinfo line and returns a corresponding SeekInfoStruct object. Here's an example seekinfo line:
  29 w=Snaps ti=02 rt=1532  t=1 i=0 r=r tp=lightning c=? rr=0-9999 a=t f=t
If the seek cannot be accepted by the user, the line identifier is "" and not "". More information about the format is available in the FICS iv_seekinfo help file.

getSeekerTitles

public int getSeekerTitles()
Returns the titles of the seeking player, ORed into an int. To find whether the player is GM, for example, use (getSeekerTitles() & SeekInfoStruct.GM) != 0.

getSeekerRating

Returns the seeker's rating.

Returns the seeker rating's provshow character. 'E' if the rating is estimated, 'P' if provisional, and ' ' if neither.

isMatchRated

public boolean isMatchRated()
Returns true if the sought match is rated, false otherwise.

getMatchType

public java.lang.String getMatchType()
Returns the sought game type. Either the name of the wild variant, or the rating type, if the variant is chess. For example - "suicide", "lightning", "blitz" etc.

getSeekerColor

public char getSeekerColor()
Returns a character specifying the desired color for the seeker. 'W' if white, 'B' if black, and '?' if the seeker doesn't care.

getOpponentMinRating

Returns true if the match will be accepted automatically, false if the seeker must confirm it manually.

isFormulaUsed

public boolean isFormulaUsed()
Returns true if in order to accept the seek, one must pass the formula of the seeker. Returns false otherwise.
